info.name: Covalent API
info.description:
The Covalent API is RESTful. The API is designed around the main resources that's available through the web interface. Sample API calls are provided next to each method using cURL.

| Parameter      | Default  | Description                                                |
|----------------|----------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| quote-currency | optional | One of usd, cad, inr, eth, eur. If not specified, use usd. |
| format         | optional | One of csv, json. If not specified, use json               |

### Supported Currencies
| Quote currency | Symbol |
|----------------|--------|
| USD            | $      |
| CAD            | $      |
| EUR            | €      |
| SGD            | $      |
| INR            | ₹      |
| JPY            | ¥      |
| VND            | ₫      |
| CNY            | ¥      |
| KRW            | ₩      |
| RUB            | ₽      |
| TRY            | ₺      |
| ETH            | Ξ      |

### Supported Networks
| Network              | Type    | ChainId |
|----------------------|---------|---------|
| Ethereum             | Mainnet | 1       |
| Polygon/Matic        | Mainnet | 137     |
| Avalanche C-Chain    | Mainnet | 43114   |
| Binance Smart Chain  | Mainnet | 56      |
| Fantom Opera         | Mainnet | 250     |
| Polygon/Matic Mumbai | Testnet | 80001   |
| Fuji C-Chain         | Testnet | 43113   |
| Kovan                | Testnet | 42      |

item.name: Class A

query.description: Set to true to return ERC721 and ERC1155 assets. Defaults to false.
Set to true to skip fetching NFT metadata, which can result in faster responses. Defaults to false and only applies when nft=true.
The requested fiat currency.
If format=csv, return a flat CSV instead of JSON responses.
Records enter a multi-stage pipeline that transforms the records into aggregated results. Supports $group and Aggregation operators.
Filters the records to pass only the documents that match the specified condition(s).
Groups input elements by the specified id expression and for each distinct grouping, outputs an element. Grouping by _date operators is also possible.
Sorts all input records and returns them in ascending or descending sorted order.
Skips over the specified number of records.Skips over the specified number of records.
Limits the number of records.

request.description: Return a list of all ERC20 and NFT token balances along with their current spot prices.

query.description: (Required) Starting block to define a block range.
Ending block to define a block range.
The specific page to be returne.
The number of results per page.
The requested fiat currency.
If format=csv, return a flat CSV instead of JSON responses.
Records enter a multi-stage pipeline that transforms the records into aggregated results. Supports $group and Aggregation operators.
Filters the records to pass only the documents that match the specified condition(s).
Groups input elements by the specified id expression and for each distinct grouping, outputs an element. Grouping by _date operators is also possible.
Sorts all input records and returns them in ascending or descending sorted order.
Skips over the specified number of records.
Limits the number of records.

The number of results per page.
The requested fiat currency.
If format=csv, return a flat CSV instead of JSON responses.
Records enter a multi-stage pipeline that transforms the records into aggregated results. Supports $group and Aggregation operators.
Filters the records to pass only the documents that match the specified condition(s).
Groups input elements by the specified id expression and for each distinct grouping, outputs an element. Grouping by _date operators is also possible.
Sorts all input records and returns them in ascending or descending sorted order.
Skips over the specified number of records.
Limits the number of records.

request.description:
Returns a list of all contracts on a blockchain along with their metadata.


| Parameter   | Description                                                                                     |
|-------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| chain_id    | Only Matic (137), BSC (56) , Avalanche (43114;43113) and Fantom Opera (250) chainIds supported. |
| contract_id | Only "all" supported right now.                                                                   |

item.description: Endpoints that return enriched blockchain data applicable to all blockchain networks, eg: balances, transactions, log events, etc.

item.name: Class B
item.description: Endpoints that for a specific protocol on a blockchain, eg: AAVE is Ethereum-only and is not applicable to other blockchain networks.

query.description: The start day of the historical price range. (YYYY-MM-DD)
The end day of the historical price range. (YYYY-MM-DD)
Sort the prices in chronological ascending order. By default, it's set to false and returns prices in chronological descending order.
The specific page to be returned.
The number of results per page.
If format=csv, return a flat CSV instead of JSON responses.
